), and beyond if you don't find exceptional upgrades (I know some level 50+ people wearing BAM's)<br><br>For those above 49, I can't say much, I'm still under 20. But I don't want the new Wizards to spaz out over all of this. Increased Damage is Hell to get, so don't even bother trying till you hit 51. But the focus items in play ARE attainable, with a bit of GFay camping<br><br>-Alexiia Corin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwhizbangdustyboots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Gnomish Advocate</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/17/02 3:08:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=732.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/whiz-side-01.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Focus items - good news for lower levels</span><hr size=1> SMRs are 1k on your server?<br><br>/boggle<br><br>I thought it was a sad day when they recently hit 3k on Vaz. <p><a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=49189" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/whiz-photo-short.gif" height=60 width=468 alt="Whizbang Dustyboots" border=0></a><br><font size=1></font><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/bottom.gif" height=12 width=239 alt="an enthralled  says 'Uoy ekil semong etah yllaeri!'" border=0 vspace=5></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaislinsteele.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AislinSteele</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://darnaxx.homestead.com/files/AislinEZ.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/17/02 3:51:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=732.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> SMR</span><hr size=1> *shrug* I got mine in GFay for 1k about a week ago. I know I ripped the guy hardcore, but I tried to talk him down to 800 and he sais &quot;1k is a good deal&quot;<br><br>Who am I to look a gift horse in the mouth? I went by my experience. If I can get one for 1k with little to no haggling, it's possible. You just have to find an eBayer that doesn't hang in GFay much<br><br>-Alexiia Corin<br><br>&quot;Actual prices and colors may vary, sale effective while supplies last&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umandosturambar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mandos Turambar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/18/02 12:51:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=732.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SMR</span><hr size=1> Where can I find a &quot;full&quot; treatment on focus items?  I have hardly been playing since Luclin, and guess I need to know if I continue to play.<br><br>Thanks! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utrippay.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trippay</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/20/02 7:14:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=732.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> freakin SMRs</span><hr size=1> I've been trying to buy a SMR for 2k on e'ci for a few months now (chanter epic), most of the time there's already a someone auctioning that they want one too.  What a pain, and now its has a focus effect? It's wonderful that I'll be able to add every lowbie caster to the endless list of rogues and chanters who I'm already in competition with. WTF Verant? like the chanter epic doesn't already have enough bottlenecks.  Was able to camp it one night... Archmagi spawned once in about 4 hours and dropped some other vt arms or something. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uusrbinperldashw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>usrbinperl dashw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/23/02 4:27:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=732.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Focus items</span><hr size=1> I know this is slightly OT, but does anyone else feel cheated that none of the TS quest armor seems to have received foci (or maybe they have and they're so rare I haven't seen it lised)?<br><br>For as much of a PitA as those items are to attain, surely at least the Robes/BPs should have a focus effect. <p><CENTER><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=157442">Xasha Maelstrom</A> (the Mage formerly known as: Usrbinperl Dashw)<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=157458">Gothique Darkmagik</A><BR><IMG SRC="http://home.columbus.rr.com/keeferfam/images/kill-maestro.gif"></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udlaren4444.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dlaren4444</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/23/02 11:29:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pu